<bug>
    <id>3865</id>
    <title>Visual Editor: Pasting formatted text into the title field yields HTML code</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Write, highlight, and copy formatted text.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Paste that text into the title bar of the post from the visual editor.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">It appears formatted.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">Switch to the HTML editor and you'll see the HTML codes.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">Switch back to the visual editor, and the HTML remains.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">If you don't switch to the HTML tab, and just publish instead, then the title shows up properly formatted on the published post.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">### Expected behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Either pasting formatted text into the title bar should yield plaintext, or else formatting from the HTML editor should be retained when switching back to the visual editor
### Actual behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">HTML formatting is lost in the title field when moving from HTML to visual editor
##### Tested on Nexus 6P, Android 6.0.1 (shown below on emulator)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">!</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">[wp-android-visual-editor-3](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7233112/13758411/bf5e8ff4-e9ff-11e5-969e-37396a22cca3.gif)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
